        "created_at": "2020-01-19T22:01:33.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>From vines planted around Chambolle. Delightful. Not a sharp edge in sight. Very smooth and rich, with notes of butterscotch, lemon curd, roasted nuts. A hint of spice gives the wine some lift. Not amazingly complex, but deep enough to hold attention. Very nice for the level. Would drink up remaining bottles.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 4,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-03T15:51:01.426Z",
