      {
        "id": 2795259,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-01-19T23:01:03.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"157731\">\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"157731\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Actually near Chambolle, but not in the commune of Chambolle: in Gilly-l\u00e8s-C\u00eeteaux! Quite a few Chambolle producers have their regional appellation holdings in that area, such as Roumier and Barthod.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I am realizing \u201caround\u201d was not the clearest word to use there! A big fan of regional wines from Gilly generally, particularly Barthod\u2019s Bourgogne.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Me too! Yet there are actually some abandoned, overgrown parcels in that sector. Which would be inconceivable a few hundred meters up the road.</p>",
